00:05:33.190 --> 00:05:34.930
Problem 18.

00:05:34.930 --> 00:05:39.290
If the sum of the consecutive
integers from minus 22 to x

00:05:39.290 --> 00:05:42.440
inclusive is 72, what
is the value of x?

00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:45.670
So this is the number-- we've
actually done a problem very,

00:05:45.670 --> 00:05:47.800
very similar to this, so it
shows you that people at the

00:05:47.800 --> 00:05:50.510
SAT, they think of a lot of
creative problems, but every

00:05:50.510 --> 00:05:52.690
now and then, they
have to repeat.

00:05:52.690 --> 00:05:54.900
So they're saying the sum of the
consecutive integers from

00:05:54.900 --> 00:05:56.670
minus 22 to x is 72.

00:05:56.670 --> 00:05:59.510
So let's think about this,
let's draw the sum.

00:05:59.510 --> 00:06:09.390
So it's minus 22, plus minus
21, plus minus 20, right?

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:16.050
Plus-- it keeps going, until
it gets to 0-- plus 0.

00:06:16.050 --> 00:06:18.910
And then-- and I'm going to go
this way, again, I'm doing

00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:21.550
that for a reason.

00:06:21.550 --> 00:06:27.280
And then you can say, plus 1,
plus 2, plus-- you keep going,

00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:39.300
and then you'd have plus 20,
plus 21, plus 22, plus 23,

00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:43.920
plus 24, all the way until
we get to x, right?

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:50.540
What you need to realize is all
the way from minus 22 to

00:06:50.540 --> 00:06:53.370
22, the sum is 0.

00:06:53.370 --> 00:06:55.000
And why is that?

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.310
Well, look at the
way I drew it.

00:06:57.310 --> 00:06:59.570
So minus 22-- we're taking the
sum of everything, right?

00:06:59.570 --> 00:07:03.150
So minus 22 is going to cancel
out with positive 22.

00:07:03.150 --> 00:07:04.850
You add those together,
you get 0.

00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:08.230
Minus 21 is going to cancel
out with positive 21.

00:07:08.230 --> 00:07:10.760
Minus 20 is going to cancel
out with positive 20.

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:11.750
And so forth, and so on.

00:07:11.750 --> 00:07:16.500
So everything-- so the sum from
minus 22 plus, bam, bam,

00:07:16.500 --> 00:07:22.060
bam, bam, all the way to plus
22, that equals 0, right?

00:07:22.060 --> 00:07:26.820
So we only get into the
positive sum once

00:07:26.820 --> 00:07:28.810
we get to 23, right?

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:32.250
So 23 plus 24 plus something,
something,

00:07:32.250 --> 00:07:34.060
something, is x, right?

00:07:34.060 --> 00:07:37.520
And we have to get to 72.

00:07:37.520 --> 00:07:39.170
And here we can just
eyeball it.

00:07:39.170 --> 00:07:44.890
23 plus 24 plus 25,
what's that?

00:07:44.890 --> 00:07:47.070
Well their average is 24,
24 times 3 is 72.

00:07:47.070 --> 00:07:48.390
Or we can just add it up.

00:07:48.390 --> 00:07:55.930
So 23 plus 24 is 47, 47
plus 25, it equals 72.

00:07:55.930 --> 00:07:59.620
So the last number that we use
in this whole range is 25.

00:07:59.620 --> 00:08:02.040
So this is x.

00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:03.520
That is x.

00:08:03.520 --> 00:08:05.750
And all we did is we said--
think about it, take the sum

00:08:05.750 --> 00:08:09.360
from minus 22, all the
way to positive 25.

00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:13.620
Everything up to negative 22,
from minus 22 to positive 22,

00:08:13.620 --> 00:08:15.490
all of those cancel out
with each other.

00:08:15.490 --> 00:08:19.470
So the sum is just going to
be 23 plus 24 plus 25.

00:08:19.470 --> 00:08:23.600
That equals 72, so
then x is 25.

